The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 LIC scam in capital

 New Delhi, Sept. 28: The CBI today unearthed fraud in one of the countrys most trusted public sector undertakings, the Life Insurance Corporation, reports our special correspondent.

 The agency, after several raids in Delhi, registered cases against five LIC agents and four officials, who allegedly diverted premiums paid by clients to fresh accounts of other policy-holders.

 The Municipal Corporation of Delhi had been sending the premiums of employees holding LIC policies under a salary saving scheme through these LIC agents, CBI spokesperson G. Mohanty said. 




